  "prompt": "Do I need to freeze my allotment in sliding round of IPU?",
  "response": "In the context of the Indian Patent Office (IPU), the term \"allotment\" likely refers to the allocation of a certain number of slots or options to submit applications or choose an IPU process. If you are referring to a specific process, such as an option in a sliding round for patent applications or other intellectual property, it's important to consult the relevant guidelines or policies provided by the IPU.\n\nTypically, whether or not you need to \"freeze\" your allotment would depend on the specific rules governing that particular round or process. This could involve completing certain paperwork or confirming your participation by a deadline.\n\nIt\u2019s best to refer to the official notifications or contact the authorities at the IPU for the most accurate and updated information, as procedures and requirements may change.",
